    item-27 at level 2: section_header: The Grave of the Slave
      item-28 at level 3: text: The cold storms of winter shall  ... his last home, he feels not the storm.
      item-29 at level 3: text: The poor slave is laid all unhee ... s not, he hears not, his cruel demand.
      item-30 at level 3: text: Not a tear, not a sigh to embalm ... for his pillow, his curtain the skies.
      item-31 at level 3: text: Poor slave! shall we sorrow that ... , to the captive, is freedom and rest.
    item-32 at level 2: section_header: The Slave Girl's Address to Her Mother
      item-33 at level 3: text: Oh! mother, weep not, though our ... e watches o'er us-mother, do not weep.
      item-34 at level 3: text: And grieve not for that dear lov ...  he must yield, as well as we, to God.
      item-35 at level 3: text: Torn from our home, our kindred  ... m is stretched to rescue, and to save.
      item-36 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-37 at level 4: text: Oh! ye who boast of Freedom's sa ... ree"- When thousands groan in hopeless
        item-38 at level 4: text: slavery
        item-39 at level 4: text: ?
      item-40 at level 3: text: Upon your land it is a cruel sta ... nd bid us rise from slavery, and live.
    item-41 at level 2: section_header: Past Joys
      item-42 at level 3: text: The friends we've loved, the hom ...  bereft, Still memory makes them dear.
      item-43 at level 3: text: And deep we feel each trifling i ... ill, That o'er some breasts doth roll?
      item-44 at level 3: text: Poor Afric's son-ah! he must fee ... that life Had twined around his heart.
      item-45 at level 3: text: His is a sorrow deeper far, Than ... , o'er which No healing balm can flow.
      item-46 at level 3: text: The mother, wife, or child he lo ... dead indeed: What for him doth remain?
      item-47 at level 3: text: A feeling of deep wretchedness C ... f other days, In painful visions roll.
      item-48 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-49 at level 4: text: His home-ah! that lov'd name recalls All that was dear to him; But
        item-50 at level 4: text: these
        item-51 at level 4: text: were scenes he'll know no more- He only
        item-52 at level 4: text: feels
        item-53 at level 4: text: they've been.
    item-54 at level 2: section_header: Prayer
      item-55 at level 3: text: This sacred right none are denie ... , And knows in prayer that he is free.
      item-56 at level 3: text: Yes, free to ask of Him, whate'e ...  Where beams thy Spirit, Lord, divine.
      item-57 at level 3: text: And Afric's children they are fr ...  The slave forgets his grief and pain;
      item-58 at level 3: text: Forgets awhile his slavish fear; ...  His hopes, his fears-for he is blest.
    item-59 at level 2: section_header: The Slave
      item-60 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-61 at level 4: text: Our sires who once in freedom's  ... hat he can ne'er be free; To feel that
        item-62 at level 4: text: his
        item-63 at level 4: text: is doomed to be A life, and deat ... e, That they still find a foe in thee?
    item-64 at level 2: section_header: The Farewell
      item-65 at level 3: text: Farewell!-but thou wilt soon for ... d busy world, Forget that I have been.
      item-66 at level 3: text: And thought of me will scarce in ... ht array, Shall pass before thine eye.
      item-67 at level 3: text: Another's lips will charm thee t ...  e'er have met In past and happy days.
      item-68 at level 3: text: And thou wilt scarcely deign to  ... in after years, On this poor offering.
      item-69 at level 3: text: Farewell-farewell!-'twere better ...  moment here, To part-and then forget.
    item-70 at level 2: section_header: A Mother's Grief
      item-71 at level 3: text: There lies the sole remaining ho ... w'd heart, The tie that bound me here.
      item-72 at level 3: text: He was the last-the loveliest, A ... which give This bursting heart relief?
      item-73 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-74 at level 4: text: There's nothing left for me to love This earth holds nothing dear, Since
        item-75 at level 4: text: he
        item-76 at level 4: text: , my sweet-my gentle one, Is now no longer here.
      item-77 at level 3: text: My poor fond heart had counted o ...  days Here strewed with fairy flowers!
      item-78 at level 3: text: Perchance 'twas wrong to love hi ... y trust, Hath called him to the skies.
      item-79 at level 3: text: He was too dear-oh! far too dear ... s burst of grief I cannot now control.
    item-80 at level 2: section_header: To the Hibernia
      item-81 at level 3: text: O, speed thee! speed thee! galla ... n's shores, The Champion of the slave.
      item-82 at level 3: text: Propitious breezes waft thee on, ... t with fervor sends A benizon to thee.
      item-83 at level 3: text: And he who fears not to commit H ...  and waves, Knowing that God is there.
      item-84 at level 3: text: He goes to raise the standard hi ...  rallying cry Of freedom to the world.
      item-85 at level 3: text: Then swift and steady be thy fli ... noble bark, The Champion of the slave.
    item-86 at level 2: section_header: Life
      item-87 at level 3: text: To see our pathway strewn with f ... nkling care Lies hidden from our view;
      item-88 at level 3: text: To cull the flowers, to love the ... dely comes Their beauties to destroy:-
      item-89 at level 3: text: Such is our life. How full of ch ... en the smile, Ere it is lost in tears.
      item-90 at level 3: text: To see the cherished things of e ... before our eyes, And silently depart;-
      item-91 at level 3: text: This is our life-and who can tel ...  heart, While close to earth we cling?
      item-92 at level 3: text: The morning of our days are brig ... eful life, How soon the dream is past!
    item-93 at level 2: section_header: The Separation
      item-94 at level 3: text: "Friend after friend departs."
      item-95 at level 3: text: And they are gone-that little ba ... sence makes, With joy, and sorrow too.
      item-96 at level 3: text: We joy that duties call them for ... t guard, And sword of truth and light.
      item-97 at level 3: text: We bid God speed their parting s ...  of duty points, May duty never pause.
      item-98 at level 3: text: And yet, we sorrow most of all,  ... h again May see these friends no more.
      item-99 at level 3: text: Their works shall live when othe ...  whelming wave, Unhonored and unnamed.
    item-100 at level 2: section_header: My Country
      item-101 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-102 at level 4: text: Oh! speak not of heathenish dark ...  we, Who claim the proud name of the "
        item-103 at level 4: text: home of the free
        item-104 at level 4: text: "! What a throb do the lov'd tie ... way a magical spell. Can the name of "
        item-105 at level 4: text: my country
        item-106 at level 4: text: "-the deeds which we sing- Be ho ...  tribute of homage she cannot command.
    item-107 at level 2: section_header: Hours of Childhood
      item-108 at level 3: text: "Blest hours of childhood! then, ... e revels gay round pleasure's throne."
      item-109 at level 3: text: Dear cherished hours, how much y ... With which we whiled those hours away.
      item-110 at level 3: text: And those we loved in early yout ... l- And joys, to which we bid farewell.
      item-111 at level 3: text: When grief and bliss are in the  ... a sigh to ye O by-gone days of memory.
    item-112 at level 2: section_header: An Appeal to Woman
      item-113 at level 3: text: Oh, woman, woman, in thy brighte ... ister's privilege, in a sister's name.
      item-114 at level 3: text: We are thy sisters-God has truly ... ister's privilege, in a sister's name.
      item-115 at level 3: text: Oh, woman!-though upon thy faire ...  name Upon the altar of immortal fame.
    item-116 at level 2: section_header: The Slave Girl's Farewell
      item-117 at level 3: text: The incident which suggested the ... ated the girl from her parent forever.
      item-118 at level 3: text: Mother, I leave thee-thou hast b ...  heart knew; Or e'er shall know again.
      item-119 at level 3: text: The sails are set-my master wait ... ve thee up, And cross the fearful sea?
      item-120 at level 3: text: Oh, let me gaze! how bright it s ... days, Beneath those bright blue skies.
      item-121 at level 3: text: The little hut where I have play ... y bank, Where I have gathered flowers.
      item-122 at level 3: inline: group group
        item-123 at level 4: text: I knew not
        item-124 at level 4: text: then
        item-125 at level 4: text: I was a slave, Or that another's ... irit's pride; Or bid my lips be still.
      item-126 at level 3: text: Who now will soothe me at my toi ... heavy lash Is raised to give the blow?
      item-127 at level 3: text: Thy fond arms press me-and I fee ... nguage now, A mother's love can speak.
      item-128 at level 3: text: Think of me, mother, as I bend M ... ssing waft, To her who prays for thee.
    item-129 at level 2: section_header: A Prayer
      item-130 at level 3: text: Father, we lift the suppliant ey ... nst not deny The children of thy love.
      item-131 at level 3: text: Unshaken faith, unwavering trust ... ugh in dust, To thee we dare to cling.
      item-132 at level 3: text: We know that thou wilt not forsa ... aviour spake; And him he came to save.
      item-133 at level 3: text: We feel the chains that bind us  ... enthrall'd, Or bid our voice be still?
      item-134 at level 3: text: No:-for thy power is all supreme ... ave shall e'en To thee for mercy turn.
